<!--
    HTML is thestandard markup language for creating Web pages.
    - Stands for Hyper Text Markup Language
    - Describes the structure of a Web Page
    - Consists of a series of elements
    - Elements tell the browser how to display the content
    - Tags labal pieces of content such as "heading", "paragraph", "table", etc.
    - Browsers do not display the HTML tags, but use them to render the content of the page
-->
<!--
    When saving an html file, set the encoding to UTF-8 (which is the preferred encoding 
    for HTML files).
    - You can use either ".htm" or ".html" as the file extension.
    
    Element with no content are empty elements. Does not have an end tag.
    - Some HTML elements will display correctly, even if you forget the end tag
      because some closing tags are considered optional.
        - <p> This is a paragraph
        - <p> This is a second paragraph

    HTML elements can be neested (elements can contain elements).
-->
<!--
    HTML Attributes
    - All HTML elements can have attributes
    - Provide additional information about an element
    - Are always specified in the start tag
    - Usually come in name/value pairs like: name="value"
    - 'style' attribute is used to specify styling of an element:
        - color
        - font
        - size
        - etc

    Quote Attributes Values are suggested but not required. Best to quote values especially
    if there are spaces in titles, descriptions, etc.
    - <a href="https://www.youtube.com">
    - <a href=https://www.youtube.com>
-->

<!DOCTYPE html> <!--Defines document to be HTML5. This is not case sensitive.-->
<html lang="en-US">
<!--Root element of an HTML page. Language declared is important for accessibility apps.-->

    <head> <!--Contains meta information about the document.-->

        <title> Page Title </title> <!--Specifies title for the document.-->
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <!--
            Typically define the document title, character set, styles, scripts, and 
            other meta info.
        -->

    </head>

    <body> <!--Contains the visible page content.-->

        <h1>My First Heading</h1> <!--Goes from h1 to h6. Most importance to least.-->
        
        <p style="color:maroon" title="I'm a tooltip">
        <!--title in paragraph becomes a tooltip when moused over.-->

            My first paragraph.
            <br> <!--Line break-->
            My second paragraph.
            <hr> <!--Horizontal rule-->
            My third paragraph.

        </p>
        
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com">Youtube Link</a> <!--Defines a link-->
        
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0b/Cat_poster_1.jpg"
            alt = "Domesticated Cats" width="104" height="142">
        
        <button>Click Me</button>

        <ul> <!--Unordered/Bullet List-->
            <li>Coffee</li>
            <li>Tea</li>
            <li>Milk</li>
        </ul>

        <ol> <!--Ordered/Numbered List-->
            <li>Coffee</li>
            <li>Tea</li>
            <li>Milk</li>
        </ol>

        <pre> <!--Defines preformatted text.-->
            This keeps

            The format

            With line breaks

            And spaces
        </pre>

    </body>

</html>